  "prompt": "What are the best places to eat vegetarian food in New Delhi?",
  "response": "New Delhi offers a plethora of excellent options for enjoying vegetarian cuisine. Here are some of the best places known for their delicious vegetarian dishes:\n\n1. **Sattvik** - Located in Select Citywalk Mall, Saket, Sattvik is known for its high-quality North Indian vegetarian food, making it a favorite amongst locals and tourists alike.\n\n2. **Saravana Bhavan** - A renowned South Indian restaurant chain, Saravana Bhavan in Connaught Place provides authentic South Indian vegetarian dishes, including dosas, idlis, and vadas.\n\n3. **Govindas** - Situated in ISKCON Temple, East of Kailash, Govindas serves pure vegetarian food in a tranquil environment. Their buffet is especially popular.\n\n4. **Veg Gulati** - Located on Pandara Road, Veg Gulati is famous for its flavorful Punjabi vegetarian dishes.\n\n5. **Burma Burma** - In Cyber Hub, Gurugram, Burma Burma offers a variety of vegetarian Burmese cuisine, tailored to suit Indian palates.\n\n6. **Imly** - An eatery in Rajendra Place, Imly offers a diverse menu spanning across various cuisines, all vegetarian, including street food and traditional Indian dishes.\n\n7. **Karma Caffe** - This cafe in Greater Kailash is known for its healthy vegetarian dishes with a modern twist.\n\n8. **Evergreen Sweet House** - Located in Green Park, this destination is perfect for vegetarian snacks, sweets, and traditional Indian meals.\n\n9. **The Potbelly Rooftop Cafe** - In Shahpur Jat, this cafe offers vegetarian Bihari cuisine with a scenic rooftop view.\n\n10. **FabCafe** - Located across multiple locations in Delhi, FabCafe offers healthy vegetarian options with a focus on organic and gluten-free ingredients.\n\nThese establishments cater to diverse tastes and preferences, ensuring that vegetarian diners have an array of delicious choices.",
